SESSIONS is same like cookies, except it save datas in your adminstrators ' webpage not client webpage. To save inforamtion temporarily, it is called session store. And to save permanently, you can save it in a database. You can also get information from session store and database. Session is mainly login page and registration.

Step 1. session_start();
Step 2. $_Session[name] = value;
Step 3. echo $_SESSION['name'];




To delete Sessions:
Step1: session_unset();  it removes all session variables.
Step2: session_destroy(); it destroys all session .